- [rumor] A receding tide near the northern town of Varcheg has revealed a jagged circle of black stone monoliths, previously hidden beneath the waves for centuries. These ancient Nordic relics, covered in unsettling etchings, have caused a wave of unease among the local Sturgians. Grand Prince Raganvad has ordered the site guarded, yet rumors of 'the deep-sea chill' have already begun to dampen the spirits of the town's merchants and laborers. The heavy silence that now hangs over the Varcheg docks is thick with the weight of an era long forgotten, leaving many to wonder what other secrets the northern coast hides. (created 14 days ago)


