- [news] King Derthert of Vlandia has officially acknowledged the unsettling discoveries at Tirby Castle, dismissing claims of an 'Iron King' as superstition while calling for a champion to silence the rumors. The King has offered to hear the pleas of any warrior capable of proving the vault is merely a relic of the past, hoping to restore order to the unnerved garrison and local peasantry. (created 17 days ago)
- [rumor] During repairs to the lower foundations of Tirby Castle, laborers broke through a false wall into a lightless, forgotten vault. Inside, they found a single suit of massive, archaic plate armor standing perfectly upright, its surface untouched by rust despite the damp. Lord Ospir quickly moved to seal the chamber, but stories of the 'Iron King' have already permeated the nearby villages. Peasants whisper that the armor belonged to a ruler who predates the Vlandian arrival, and the garrison's morale has faltered as men claim to hear the rhythmic clanking of metal echoing from the depths during the new moon. (created 20 days ago)
- [rumor] A receding tide near the northern town of Varcheg has revealed a jagged circle of black stone monoliths, previously hidden beneath the waves for centuries. These ancient Nordic relics, covered in unsettling etchings, have caused a wave of unease among the local Sturgians. Grand Prince Raganvad has ordered the site guarded, yet rumors of 'the deep-sea chill' have already begun to dampen the spirits of the town's merchants and laborers. The heavy silence that now hangs over the Varcheg docks is thick with the weight of an era long forgotten, leaving many to wonder what other secrets the northern coast hides. (created 24 days ago)


