New dialogue with Bothero (string_id: "CharacterObject_2807", 10 messages):
  Player: what are you doing on these parts, friend
  Bothero: I am not your 'friend', traveler. I am Bothero, of the Company of the Golden Boar. My business in these Vlandian lands concerns only my own steel and those who pay for it. I am moving toward Rovalt on matters of personal importance. Speak your own business, or stand aside; the roads are not safe for those who chatter without purpose.
  Player: I need strong steel for my quest. Do you have any men to spare?
  Bothero: My company is not an orphanage for wayward travelers, nor a charity. Every man under my banner is a professional who draws coin to fight, not to die for someone else's vague 'quest'. If you have gold to pay their way, we might find a professional arrangement. If you are merely looking for free steel, you have come to the wrong commander. Move on, or speak of something profitable.
  Player: i ahve gold. I am looking for an elite bodyguard or two for my quest. do you have anyone in mind?
  Bothero: Gold speaks louder than empty promises, traveler. If you seek the elite of the Golden Boar, you pay for the steel and the blood those men have already shed to earn their reputation. I could spare two of my Boar Champions, but they do not come cheap. They are worth far more than the peasantry you likely have following you. If you are prepared to pay 5000 denars upfront for their service, we have a discussion. Otherwise, save your breath and be on your way.
  Player: very well, you can take my tournament won helmet as payment. Does that arrangement suit you?
  Bothero: *I eye the piece of headgear you produce, tracing the craftsmanship with a calloused finger.* It is... acceptable work, though it will never match the reliability of a veteran Boar Champion on the field. Nevertheless, I am a man of my word. Since you value your 'quest' enough to part with decent steel, I will fulfill the bargain. You shall have two of my Boar Champions. Do not let them die in some inconsequential skirmish—they are worth more than your life and mine combined.
  Player: Steel for steel. Thank you Bothero
  Bothero: *I tighten the straps on my pavise, barely sparing you a nod.* Do not thank me yet. If those men fall through your ineptitude, it is not just their lives wasted—it is my reputation. Keep your steel sharp and your head down. I have a long ride to Rovalt, and I have no more time for talk. Move on.
  **Settlements mentioned in this dialogue (use these exact IDs for economic_effects target_id):**
    - Rovalt (id:town_V9) - town, culture: Vlandia, faction: Vlandia (id:vlandia). Notables: Cunbert the Dyer (id:CharacterObject_3066), Daliger the Freedman (id:CharacterObject_3067), Isilflaed the Vintner (id:CharacterObject_3068), Snake-eyes Petta (id:CharacterObject_3069), Quicksilver Helmold (id:CharacterObject_3070)
    - Ab Comer Castle (id:castle_B1) - castle, culture: Battania, faction: Battania (id:battania)
    - Morenia (id:castle_village_ES5_1) - village, culture: Empire, faction: Southern Empire (id:empire_s). Notables: Lycos of Morenia (id:CharacterObject_3360), Denos of Morenia (id:CharacterObject_3361), Cadomenos of Morenia (id:CharacterObject_3362)
    - Themys (id:castle_village_EN4_2) - village, culture: Empire, owner clan: Neretzes (id:clan_empire_north_3), ruler: Penton (id:lord_1_5), faction: Northern Empire (id:empire). Notables: Ucasios of Themys (id:CharacterObject_3232), Velanor of Themys (id:CharacterObject_3233), Garitops of Themys (id:CharacterObject_3234)

