New dialogue with Lucand (string_id: "lord_4_25", 19 messages):
  Player: I have found the hideout. Ospir has granted me acces to your armory - i need a twohanded sword to make  frontal assault
  Player: Ospir sent me to get a weapon from the armory. i need at least a tier 5 longsword to make a succesfull frontal assault on the hideout where the iron imposter hides.
  Lucand: I will give you my finest sword, a tier 5 arming sword, to aid you in your assault. Use it wisely, and let the king’s mandate guide you.
  Player: Ia m sorry but i need a twohanded sword for this. 
  Lucand: I’m sorry, but I have no two‑handed sword to spare. The only heavy blade I possess is this arming sword. You may use it, or bring your own if you wish.
  Player: I humbly ask that you look again for any twohanded sword. Ospir told me that the armory would have one
  Lucand: I have searched the armory again, Amaldulf, and find no two‑handed blade to spare. The only heavy sword I possess is this tier 5 arming sword. Use it as you will, or bring your own if you require a larger blade.
  Player: Do you have any twohanded weapons in the armory?
